      "content": "## Mock Interview & AI Coaching (ALL ISSUES FIXED Feb 10)\n**Flow**: Setup (role + JD) → Interview (AI voice Q&A) → Analysis (video + voice) → History\n\n**Questions**: 25 AI-generated role-specific (cached, randomized) | Fallback: 8 scripted role-adapted | Greeting: Natural \"Alex\" intro + self-intro prompt\n\n**Audio Pipeline**:\n- **TTS**: OpenAI nova questions + `tts_cache` table (MP3 cached by content hash) — zero tokens on cache hit; 6-provider fallback chain; goodbye fire-and-forget (8s cap, never awaits)\n- **Recognition**: Real-time during recording; useRef mirrors capture async callback state (fixes stale closure bug)\n- **Transcription**: OpenAI Whisper (WAV/MP3/WebM multipart) → full ASR fallback chain wired to voice-respond endpoint\n- **Silence detection**: 3.5s auto-triggers next question via `AudioBufferSourceNode.onended`\n- **Video analysis**: Frame capture every 5s → GPT-4o vision for body language at interview END, async, cached; requires HTTP URLs (not base64)\n- **Voice analysis**: Tone, pace, clarity, confidence scoring on end\n- **Dynamic follow-ups**: Rewrote interviewer prompt to probe vague answers, ask specifics, explore interesting points before advancing\n- **Full transcript**: Both \"Alex\" (interviewer) and candidate messages with color-coded avatars and action labels post-interview\n\n**Feedback** (Phase 3 redesign):\n- Answer Content | Communication & Speech | Body Language format (matching practice sessions)\n- Bonus sections: Interview Arc, communication trends, per-question STAR scores, technical depth\n- Threshold: 1 candidate turn minimum | Returns `no_feedback` flag on backend 400 (zero answers)\n\n**iOS Fixes**: Web Audio API + AudioContext on gesture, `muted`, `playsInline`, `webkit-playsinline=\"\"`, `isolation: isolate` + `overflow-hidden` parent, camera auto-on via useEffect\n\n**STALE CLOSURE BUG (FIXED Feb 10)**: MediaRecorder/AudioBuffer async callbacks captured stale state. **Fix**: useRef mirrors for `mockLiveTranscript`, `voiceMode`, `candidateRecording` — all async callbacks read from refs (fresh)",
